This paper deals with integer parameter estimation in a linear model, which is a problem commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and data science (cs.DS) communities. The use of sphere decoding and the LLL reduction algorithm are also common techniques in these fields. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the computational complexity of these algorithms, which is a topic studied in computer science theory (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the success probability of the Babai point, which is a statistical measure and could be relevant to the statistical inference (cs.SI) community.
